This is fascinating.  The OutOfMemoryError seems to have made java "forget" the
current locale.  Notice in the log entries, that the date on the entry is
formatted according to the current locale.  After the OutOfMemoryErrors, it is
no longer formatting the log entry dates.  The other two errors (one in
resources shutdown, the other in the preference store), are caused by failure to
infer the locale on calls to Date.toString() (date is added "for free" by the
java property file implementation).

Very interesting indeed.

Not much we can do about the OutOfMemory or the Locale problems, but we should
investigate the SaveManager code where we are writing the master table. We have
other problems in this area and they could be related.

See also bug 3128.
